// HW: Guessing Game Pseudocode assignment

Start

Declare an integer variable called randomInt
Declare an integer variable called attempts
Declare an integer variable called userInput, set to -1

Print welcome and title message
Print a prompt explaining that the user has 7 attempts to enter a correct guess

Enter a while loop, exits if userInput = 0

	Assign a random number between 1 and 100 to randomInt

	Enter a do-while loop, exits if attempts >= 7 or randomInt = userInput
		Prompt user to input guess, formatted to be numbered by using the attempts variable
		Gather user input, validate against invalid input (integer only)
		Increment attempts

	If randomInt = userInput
		Print winning condition
	Else
		Print losing condition

	Reset attempts and set userInput to -1

	Prompt user to enter 0 to exit, press anything else to restart
	
	Gather user input, validate against invalid input (integer only)

	End loop

Print exit message

End
	
